criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  be diagnosed with unilateral breast cancer;

          -  be submitted to surgical and radiation treatment as part of the treatment for breast
             cancer.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with neurological or orthopedic diseases that could impair the upper limb
             movements

          -  bilateral breast cancer;

          -  prior thoracic radiotherapy;

          -  presence of distant metastasis.
